-- Mask refresh queue: entities whose CONSENSUS participation changed and whose
-- highway_mask therefore needs recomputing.
--
-- Why this exists (2026-07-21): highway_mask_refresh derives a mask purely from an
-- entity's consensus edges, so the exact refresh set after a fold is "every subject
-- and object written by that fold". That set was being tracked client-side in a
-- HashSet<Hash128> capped at 8,388,608 (ConsensusAccumulatingWriter); any ingest
-- larger than the cap threw the set away and fell back to highway_mask_rebuild --
-- a full pass over every entity in the substrate. Every large source therefore paid
-- a multi-minute full rebuild, which is batch-rebuild-as-a-class, the thing the
-- substrate forbids: the fold-time refresh is the intended mechanism and the full
-- rebuild is a rare REGENERATE tool for highway bit renumbering only.
--
-- Capturing the set here instead makes it exact, unbounded, and deduplicated by the
-- primary key, with no client memory and no overflow path.
--
-- SUPERSEDED ON THE INGEST PATH (2026-07-21). The fold no longer queues here and
-- no ingest drains it: highway_mask_deposit runs INLINE in every lane, which is
-- O(pairs the fold already holds in RAM) with zero consensus re-reads, versus this
-- queue's O(touched entities x consensus probes) recompute in one serial pass at
-- the end of a run. What survives here is the REPAIR path, which deposit cannot
-- express: deposit only OR-accumulates, so anything that must CLEAR bits --
-- per-source eviction removing an entity's last governed edge -- queues the
-- affected entities here and calls highway_mask_drain(), whose
-- highway_mask_refresh recomputes each mask from scratch and can therefore clear.
-- (highway_mask_rebuild remains the full REGENERATE tool for bit renumbering.)
--
-- UNLOGGED: pure derived work-queue. Losing it on a crash costs a regenerate, never
-- data — and the masks it would have written are themselves recomputable from
-- consensus at any time (recompute-not-accumulate).
CREATE UNLOGGED TABLE IF NOT EXISTS highway_mask_dirty (
    id bytea PRIMARY KEY
);
